    "description": {
      "en": {
        "provenance": "imported",
        "value": "Pelvic Organ Prolapse (POP) and Cervical Cancer (CC) Screening, Management and referral as per National Guidelines, with special focus on women and girls from marginalized, vulnerable and under-served communities .Offer Health response to Gender Based Violence (GBV) with first aid at community level health facility and referral to appropriate center for higher intervention.Capacity building of Health care facilities, hospitals and personnel to provide facility appropriate services in POP and Cervical Cancer under Health system Strengthening focus of project.Support selected birthing centers in Sarlahi and Rautahat districts by building Eco-toiletContribute to reduce occurrence of POP and CC in communities, among young and vulnerable women and girls through awareness sessions and advocacy efforts with key stakeholders for facilitating service availability and utilization (eg: political/ social/faith based/religious leaders, media and others)"
      },
      "ne": null
    },
